The paper proposes a memory-based policy for robotic applications, which suggests that it falls under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of reinforcement learning and attention mechanism indicates that it also belongs to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The proposed policy deals with visual observations, which suggests that it falls under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of attention mechanism and reinforcement learning also suggests that it belongs to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it also belongs to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
